Calculate wall U-value¶

The calculation of the U value is based on the 3CL method, which depends on the type of wall and information available for the wall insulation and contruction period. The combinations of "PORTEUR" and "REVETEMENT_EXT", presented in the previous part, were associated to the 3CL construction techniques.

Non insulated wall and base value¶

Uw_0¶

  • The values were calculated based on the wall type and thickness
  • These values are already described in the file: DISPOSITIFS_MUR-export_avec_U0.xlsx

Insulation unknown¶

Uw_inc¶

Calculates Uph in case the presence of insulation is unknown

  • The values of P3 from 75-77 are always equal to those of "Autres" 78-82
  • P6 has each time just one value for "Effet joule" et "Autres", which will facilitate the storage of both of them later

Uw_R¶

In [20]:
# generalization
def calculate_Uw_R(row, name_col, dict_cols):
    if row['EP_ISOLANT'] > 0:
        if (row['ISOLANT'] == "ITI_LM") or (row['ISOLANT'] == "ITE_LM"):
            conduct = 0.04
        if row['ISOLANT'] == 'ITE_POL':
            conduct = 0.03
        if row['ISOLANT'] == 'ITI_AIR':
            conduct = 0.025
        Uw_R = 1 / ( (1 / row[dict_cols[name_col]] ) + (row['EP_ISOLANT'] / 100) / conduct)

        return Uw_R
    else:
        return np.nan

Uw_E¶

In [23]:
def calculate_Uw_E(row, name_col, dict_cols):
    if row['EP_ISOLANT'] > 0:
        Uw_E = 1 / ( (1 / row[dict_cols[name_col]] ) + (row['EP_ISOLANT'] / 100) / 0.04)

        return Uw_E
    else:
        return np.nan
